<p>This regex works well for me to validate password:</p>

<pre class=3D"lang-js s-code-block"><code data-highlighted=3D"yes" class=3D=
"hljs language-javascript">/[ !<span class=3D"hljs-string">"#$%&amp;'()*+,-=
./:;&lt;=3D&gt;?@[\\\]^_`{|}~]/
</span></code></pre>

<p>This list of special characters (including white space and punctuation) =
was taken from here: <a href=3D"https://www.owasp.org/index.php/Password_sp=
ecial_characters" rel=3D"nofollow noreferrer">https://www.owasp.org/index.p=
hp/Password_special_characters</a>. It was changed a bit, cause backslash (=
'\') and closing bracket (']') had to be escaped for proper work of the reg=
ex. That's why two additional backslash characters were added.</p>
